AB  - Pinellas County is a tourist oriented county with 53% of its employment aimed at the service sector. Indeed, the whole economy of the county is oriented to seasonal visitors and vacationers. The principal reasons for the visitors coming to Pinellas are the climate and the beaches. The factors of severe beach erosion, the crenulated embayment and the high cost of nourishment make the construction of structural improvement (breakwater) an economically attractive alternative. The major objective of constructing the breakwater was to decrease the long-term nourishment rate. A detached breakwater accomplishes this by creating a lower energy zone (less wave action) in the lee of the structure. This decreases the loss of material and even causes an accumulation of material taken from the alongshore drift. The second objective is to stabilize the beach width, which will enhance the storm protection and recreational benefits of the beach area. The third objective of the detached breakwater system is to keep the erosional effects to adjacent shorelines to a minimum.
