AB  - Developments in the Rotterdam port area and the predictions of extreme high water levels, have led to the re-examination of old plans to construct a storm surge barrier in the New Waterway as an alternative to the raising of the dykes. Five international consortia were asked in the summer of 1987 to pesent an offer on the basis of their own conceptual design for the realization of this barrier. The final selection was made in 1989 in favour of the BMK Barrier Design and Construction Group. The paper gives a review of the design philosophy and basic design principles. Particular emphasis is given to the risk and probability analysis, which formed an integral part of the design. The structural elements of the barrier together with the actual status of the construction are described. Special attention is given to the works in the river, comprising the support of the barrier and the bed protection, which required unprecedented accuracy under difficult conditions of tidal currents and heavy shipping traffic.
