AB  - The Gold Coast Seaway entrance stabilization scheme, the first such scheme in Australia to incorporate a permanent sand-bypassing system, is described. The entrance is located on a high-wave-energy shoreline experiencing large-scale sand movements. The sand-bypassing system used a unique arrangement of ten jet pumps along a fixed trestle and had successfully bypassed more than 1.2 million cubic metres of sand by the end of 1988. A safe navigable entrance channel to the Broadwater has been provided without adversely affecting nearby beaches. (D.W.T.)
